content: Tried the regular version. Liked it and wanted more features, so upgraded to PRO version. Works great on my DROID. Quite a few more features than the simpler version. Well worth the measly $1.99 + tax. Money well spent. There are videos on YouTube of it in action. Nice to monitor your WSJT-X in action, via your WIFI.
Works well BUT it doesn't work with JT Alert. There is a cumbersome workaround but I personally think that this should be mentioned in the app description.
replyContent: Actually the latest JTAlert version has fixed the packet forwarding feature (so no cumbersome work-around). Tell JTAlert to forward data to your phone's IP and you're done. One user reported he had to save, close, and restart JTAlert. We should have updated the help webpage by now. Thanks for the (unintended) reminder.

content: Very awesome! I can't always be at my ham station but with this app I know when a Country I need shows up on the band. A must have if you're chasing awards. Doug W6TY
Setup as per non pay app and it will not connect. Non pay app works
replyContent: The default settings will prohibit both apps from running concurrently, because they will both try to access the same network port (2237). Please make sure one is completely shut down before starting the other. If this doesn't solve the problem or if you need more assistance please email: feedback@feotec.com. We are happy to help, even on a Sunday.
